📍 Gandhinagar, Gujarat
📅 16th February 2026

Students of Kadi Sarva Vishwavidyalaya (KSV), Gandhinagar from the M. M. Patel Students Research Project Cell, KSV, attended the IndiaSkills Regional Competition 2026, Gandhinagar, Gujarat, as participants.

The competition brought together talented participants from across the Western Region of India, Gujarat, Maharashtra, Rajasthan, and Goa, along with the Union Territories of Dadra & Nagar Haveli and Daman & Diu, who showcased exceptional expertise across diverse professional skill domains.

Domains Showcased
Participants showcased excellence in key areas including Construction, Creative Design, IT & Digital Skills, and Health Services, reflecting strong skill development, innovation, and industry-level precision.

🧑🏻‍🎓👩🏻‍🎓 Student Representatives – M. M. Patel Students Research Project Cell, KSV
• Aayush Pandya, CE, LDRP-ITR, KSV
• Antra Gajjar, CE, LDRP-ITR, KSV
• Bhagyashree Jadeja, CE, LDRP-ITR, KSV
• Chrisha Dabhi, CE, LDRP-ITR, KSV
• Dev Kansara, CE, LDRP-ITR, KSV
• HARSH PAREKH, EC, LDRP-ITR, KSV
• Kanksha Buch, CE, LDRP-ITR, KSV
• Mahi Parmar, CE, LDRP-ITR, KSV
• Pragati Varu, CE, LDRP-ITR, KSV
• Rudr Halvadiya, CE, LDRP-ITR, KSV
• Yajurshi Velani, CE, LDRP-ITR, KSV
• Yash Kumavat, CE, LDRP-ITR, KSV

🌟 Student Insights and Experience from the Event:
Attending the competition provided them with valuable exposure to industry-level standards and real-world performance expectations. They expressed that witnessing the dedication, technical expertise, and professionalism of the participants was both inspiring and motivating.

Interacting with domain experts helped them understand the depth of preparation and discipline required for such prestigious competitions. The experience enhanced their communication skills, broadened their awareness of national and global platforms, and encouraged them to actively prepare for future competitive opportunities.

We extend our sincere gratitude to Kadi Sarva Vishwavidyalaya (KSV) and SVKM for providing this enriching opportunity and continuously supporting student exposure to national-level platforms.

Such initiatives truly bridge academic learning with real-world excellence and professional growth.
